---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Gavin Robert Foster">

  <!-- ── Hero ── -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="hero-inner">
        <div class="hero-text">
          <p class="hero-eyebrow">PhD Candidate &middot; Philosophy &middot; Purdue University</p>
          <h1>Gavin<br/>Robert<br/>Foster</h1>
          <p class="hero-sub">
            I work on the evolution and development of social cognition: how humans
            and other animals come to represent minds, knowledge, and desire. My research
            spans philosophy of mind and cognitive science, comparative and developmental
            psychology, and Kant's theoretical philosophy.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-links">
            <a href="/research" class="btn-primary">Research</a>
            <a href="/publications" class="btn-secondary">Publications</a>
            <a href="/cv" class="btn-secondary">CV</a>
          </div>
          <p class="hero-affil">
            Affiliate, <span>Social and Cognitive Origins Group</span><br/>
            Department of Psychology &amp; Brain Sciences, Johns Hopkins University
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-photo-wrap">
          <div class="hero-photo">
            <img src="/photo.jpg" alt="Gavin Robert Foster" />
          </div>
          <div class="hero-photo-caption">Purdue University · West Lafayette, IN</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Selected publications ── -->
  <section class="selected-pubs">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Selected Publications</p>
      <div class="card-list">

        <div class="card">
          <p class="card-meta">Forthcoming · Cognition</p>
          <p class="card-title">Metarepresentation and the puzzle of desire-attribution</p>
          <p class="card-desc">Foster, G. R., &amp; Westra, E.</p>
          <div class="card-tags">
            <span class="tag">Theory of Mind</span>
            <span class="tag">Metarepresentation</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <p class="card-meta">2026 · PLOS ONE</p>
          <p class="card-title"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0341872" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Do dogs rationally infer the causes of failed actions?</a></p>
          <p class="card-desc">Bastos, A. P. M., Foster, G. R., &amp; Krupenye, C.</p>
          <div class="card-tags">
            <span class="tag">Comparative Cognition</span>
            <span class="tag">Dogs</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <p class="card-meta">2025 · Philosophical Psychology</p>
          <p class="card-title"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1080/09515089.2025.2556845" target="_blank" rel="noopener">From Monkeys to Infants: The Empirical Challenges Facing Mental Fictionalism</a></p>
          <p class="card-desc">Foster, G. R.</p>
          <div class="card-tags">
            <span class="tag">Fictionalism</span>
            <span class="tag">Folk Psychology</span>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
      <p class="pubs-more"><a href="/publications">All publications &rarr;</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Research areas ── -->
  <section class="areas">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Research Areas</p>
      <div class="areas-list">
        <div class="area-item">
          <div class="area-num">01</div>
          <div class="area-content">
            <h3>Theory of Mind &amp; Mindreading</h3>
            <p>How humans and other animals attribute knowledge, belief, and desire: the logical problem of mindreading and factive accounts of knowledge attribution in primates.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="area-item">
          <div class="area-num">02</div>
          <div class="area-content">
            <h3>Comparative &amp; Developmental Cognition</h3>
            <p>Empirical and conceptual research on animal minds, from monkeys and great apes to dogs and human infants, including hands-on experimental work in comparative psychology.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="area-item">
          <div class="area-num">03</div>
          <div class="area-content">
            <h3>Norm Psychology</h3>
            <p>Whether non-human primates are genuinely normative creatures. I argue that the absence of third-party punishment among primates is no good reason to deny them a norm psychology, since even humans often sustain social norms without it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="area-item">
          <div class="area-num">04</div>
          <div class="area-content">
            <h3>Bounded Rationality</h3>
            <p>Groundwork for a bounded epistemic non-consequentialism that is Kantian in spirit, applying Kantian epistemology to the philosophy of inquiry while taking seriously the boundedness of human cognition.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="area-item">
          <div class="area-num">05</div>
          <div class="area-content">
            <h3>Kant on Moral Psychology &amp; Education</h3>
            <p>A "synthetic Kantian" reconstruction of Kant's moral psychology and education, reconciling his account of childhood and moral development with contemporary developmental and moral psychology.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Contact strip ── -->
  <section class="contact-strip">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Get in Touch</p>
      <p>I'm always happy to discuss research, collaboration, or questions about my work.</p>
      <p class="contact-email">foste362 AT purdue DOT edu</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
/* ── Hero ── */
.hero {
  padding: 5rem 0 4rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
.hero-inner {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
  gap: 4rem;
  align-items: start;
}
.hero-eyebrow {
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--accent);
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
}
.hero h1 {
  font-size: 4.5rem;
  line-height: 1.0;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}
.hero-sub {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  color: var(--ink-light);
  max-width: 480px;
  line-height: 1.7;
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
}
.hero-links {
  display: flex;
  gap: 0.75rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
}
.hero-affil {
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  color: var(--ink-faint);
  line-height: 1.6;
  border-left: 2px solid var(--accent-light);
  padding-left: 0.75rem;
}
.hero-affil span { color: var(--accent); }

.hero-photo-wrap { text-align: center; }
.hero-photo {
  width: 280px;
  background: var(--bg-alt);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  overflow: hidden;
}
.hero-photo img {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  display: block;
}
.hero-photo-caption {
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  color: var(--ink-faint);
  margin-top: 0.6rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
}

/* ── Buttons ── */
.btn-primary {
  display: inline-block;
  background: var(--accent);
  color: #fff;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  padding: 0.6em 1.4em;
  border-radius: 2px;
  transition: background 0.15s;
}
.btn-primary:hover { background: var(--ink); color: #fff; text-decoration: none; }

.btn-secondary {
  display: inline-block;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  color: var(--ink-light);
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  padding: 0.6em 1.4em;
  border-radius: 2px;
  transition: border-color 0.15s, color 0.15s;
}
.btn-secondary:hover { border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }

/* ── Research areas ── */
.areas {
  padding: 3rem 0;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
.areas-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
.area-item {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 60px 1fr;
  gap: 1.5rem;
  padding: 1.35rem 0;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  align-items: baseline;
}
.area-item:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
.area-num {
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-size: 2rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  line-height: 1;
  color: var(--accent-light);
}
.area-content h3 {
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
}
.area-content p {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: var(--ink-light);
  line-height: 1.6;
}

/* ── Selected pubs ── */
.selected-pubs { padding: 4rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
.pubs-more { margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 0.9rem; }

/* ── Contact ── */
.contact-strip { padding: 4rem 0; }
.contact-strip p { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--ink-light); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
.contact-strip p.contact-email {
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-size: 1.6rem;
  color: var(--accent);
  margin-bottom: 0;
}

/* ── Responsive ── */
@media (max-width: 820px) {
  .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .hero-photo { margin: 0 auto; }
  .hero h1 { font-size: 3rem; }
  .area-item { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.5rem; padding: 1.5rem 0; }
  .area-num { font-size: 2.2rem; }
}
</style>
